[
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
    "hash": "3cea07ac5b3d5c27f3b87fb724c38fd8c32bf1ab9fa665f52a544060e851e318"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "I know {it is} so of a truth: but how should man be just with God? {with God: or, before God?}",
    "hash": "b02d116696030f7837908520a3fb0711fc87800f9015c3e96c65c670e63d5888"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "If he will contend with him, he cannot answer him one of a thousand.",
    "hash": "3315d40fa5c0f0c53bbc964f804a91f00601b7ec05e6952d3dcc0caee5de99d3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "{He is} wise in heart, and mighty in strength: who hath hardened {himself} against him, and hath prospered?",
    "hash": "37c73e5842ba3b6456732e39141df446558373ad166b6bec3e6b89c4163e8cb2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Which removeth the mountains, and they know not: which overturneth them in his anger.",
    "hash": "d37142f5fe68eecb167f92a4a5528d8fc98d90f4eb714fa0075746ad8b8f3212"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Which shaketh the earth out of her place, and the pillars thereof tremble.",
    "hash": "d15786528404341102dcc1105c40453f8db20b74ef5bdb3f01d7701a5fa1aa8f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Which commandeth the sun, and it riseth not; and sealeth up the stars.",
    "hash": "c5d8b5c634bdd536e8f7d5ed0cb9a3264f072da70765af0c41ddd7f3f06da2fa"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Which alone spreadeth out the heavens, and treadeth upon the waves of the sea. {waves: Heb. heights}",
    "hash": "d8c5bdc110b85fc58567b7e7b9049ae2ca424c9d5dc94ceb67aae58a1b57c6d9"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Which maketh Arcturus, Orion, and Pleiades, and the chambers of the south. {Arcturus...: Heb. Ash, Cesil, and Cimah}",
    "hash": "28d6b3b6eaf7b3c16d45e10797aa992695ed0dd2ea5b9dd3637f3c91e906d6e9"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Which doeth great things past finding out; yea, and wonders without number.",
    "hash": "13c0b70d60a4384474a8910ee36cebaa538d90c0579a7d00369c6b6904e0cd79"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Lo, he goeth by me, and I see {him} not: he passeth on also, but I perceive him not.",
    "hash": "b8886d565c8aaf008ab738d57ccd3bf01d239aefb2a80ef90a5863d8fd9ad2b9"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Behold, he taketh away, who can hinder him? who will say unto him, What doest thou? {hinder...: Heb. turn him away?}",
    "hash": "acf388a6aa924ae14af4dbc28fed6f208897c3e14956d9cd12953c337a591d63"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "{If} God will not withdraw his anger, the proud helpers do stoop under him. {proud...: Heb. helpers of pride, or, strength}",
    "hash": "2cbeae27bcd4bbc732ee8813abe28a8bd78260887eb7db57683178c94fb8acda"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "How much less shall I answer him, {and} choose out my words {to reason} with him?",
    "hash": "402023db437277c5d82631af5346962b5364c5c8d221387b8e664a23b4fcf634"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Whom, though I were righteous, {yet} would I not answer, {but} I would make supplication to my judge.",
    "hash": "253dc9013a3d6af766f75ccf1daf0923548618f015fe029f8f4efc24f5932e0a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "If I had called, and he had answered me; {yet} would I not believe that he had hearkened unto my voice.",
    "hash": "e3c80b58c74d9f4e2536b2c876cf339241bd2baf36a988d27f489c72ddde075e"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For he breaketh me with a tempest, and multiplieth my wounds without cause.",
    "hash": "c30849c0b4d4a43372dc52479e9d747a0e858f5b7eae6fc80c152e85dcb45707"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "He will not suffer me to take my breath, but filleth me with bitterness.",
    "hash": "e5890401d3e1ee2c2b2d31ad6e7d4f9a3de30906f73f42f0b5ddf029b5e597c0"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "If {I speak} of strength, lo, {he is} strong: and if of judgment, who shall set me a time {to plead}?",
    "hash": "265869ffaa39c7773b60afcad336e75b15c94c048cb60f711e9c54a3c931f1b8"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "If I justify myself, mine own mouth shall condemn me: {if I say}, I {am} perfect, it shall also prove me perverse.",
    "hash": "0273a23f2967a71cbe0dcce9e1d30da09299c10baf589aaaebb9336bafacf0bb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "{Though} I {were} perfect, {yet} would I not know my soul: I would despise my life.",
    "hash": "bd20bff6ee2da771ff004edbdca4c5819933c3a35224d2d2f79acd7bdc93c118"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "This {is} one {thing}, therefore I said {it}, He destroyeth the perfect and the wicked.",
    "hash": "5d481828598a598e1ca6eeb4853258cc786030d0fd03819b859153a87c34071c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "If the scourge slay suddenly, he will laugh at the trial of the innocent.",
    "hash": "6971dcb9eca66fc5aad0c0d609663809bf84801fa2303b399ddde799c5fbb0f9"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked: he covereth the faces of the judges thereof; if not, where, {and} who {is} he?",
    "hash": "027d36b73637ff83bb1480f62e574971077cab9452a3b560a29e6f46c5dd2d1f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Now my days are swifter than a post: they flee away, they see no good.",
    "hash": "7f748d462017b989580fbd5b811ca04daa99b1081d1b4efa2f35377db407ec62"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "They are passed away as the swift ships: as the eagle {that} hasteth to the prey. {swift...: or, ships of Ebeh: Heb. ships of desire}",
    "hash": "803afd0e8a36187a8d1b8a943d3c472e50ce0631a6affc0b87f42d28a4010ab6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "If I say, I will forget my complaint, I will leave off my heaviness, and comfort {myself}:",
    "hash": "4b97a28473b0e52dfee2c95f0c5c8595b7e7cd64f7162f5bf65d687a5622a6d3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "I am afraid of all my sorrows, I know that thou wilt not hold me innocent.",
    "hash": "fc18551611059924232534d3b8e64dc43e8a80fc964f2c42991a19a2f1ef7774"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "{If} I be wicked, why then labour I in vain?",
    "hash": "074ad4ecb23a0e464aa6270da8cf3afeb702f673d442a4962a249b700cadf02d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "If I wash myself with snow water, and make my hands never so clean;",
    "hash": "aa46763bfb98758e31eb90cd7d6270e7d5d067e3a1b858c9e422d628979de94c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.31",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Yet shalt thou plunge me in the ditch, and mine own clothes shall abhor me. {abhor...: or, make me to be abhorred}",
    "hash": "3a5007257f99cb3606ad3d46dab61590a78ff7d1388bc64fd1190a513e8a03b2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.32",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "For {he is} not a man, as I {am, that} I should answer him, {and} we should come together in judgment.",
    "hash": "6a355de381a8058cb6d3f54599a2f8c451dbea06c116b4310766078f9ccaf43d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.33",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Neither is there any daysman betwixt us, {that} might lay his hand upon us both. {any...: Heb. one that should argue} {daysman: or, umpire}",
    "hash": "ead9cb88f53234ca2adf09f303d2f04e15f25ba6e4051ba21ccf372088689c9b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.34",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Let him take his rod away from me, and let not his fear terrify me:",
    "hash": "57691f28a3eb55c922a7bcb1990367de907282ac16c2b31b94e1cf03933b4455"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.9.35",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "{Then} would I speak, and not fear him; but {it is} not so with me. {it is...: Heb. I am not so with myself}",
    "hash": "54a7fb26eb4293a40c43f7c97ced74fc644f1a5d04b6a6c9345fd17fe30ae938"
  }
]